expanding views of africa meet the curator events at stanford expanding views of africa meet the curator facebook twitter email print add to calendar the arts of africa date from the beginning of humanity to the present and express universal and timeless ideas the newly reinstalled african art galleries feature more than 200 objects and are designed to expand conventional ways of considering african art and culture the galleries offer historical depth geographic and chronological representation ranging from the contemporary times to ancient egypt and a diverse range of media join barbara thompson ph d the center's phyllis wattis curator of the arts of africa and the americas for a discussion about the reinstallation of the african galleries thompson speaks about new directions in collecting and displaying the arts of africa and its diaspora when thursday september 15 2011 6 00 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading international arts contact 723 3469 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 285 28581 more info last modified august 30 2011
